{"serial": "26017", "department_serial": 25, "code": "OS6003", "class": "B", "name": {"en": "Fourier Optics", "ch": "傅氏光學"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": ""}, "instructor": {"en": ["Sun, Ching-Cherng"], "ch": ["孫慶成"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 2, "session": ["A", "B", "C"]}, "loc": {"building": "IL", "room": "116"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "光電科學與工程學系", "en": "Department of Optics and Photonics"}, "system": {"ch": "碩博同修", "en": "Master/Doctoral Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "英語", "en": "English"}, "card": {"ch": "部份使用", "en": "Optional"}, "assigned": 57, "selected": 18, "remark": {"ch": "", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "傅氏光學是光波在自由空間或光學系統中傳播的基礎理論，以較簡易的方式處理干涉與繞射的問題，是光學資訊處理與全像光學的重要基本課程。", "en": "“Fourier Optics is a fundamental course dealing with the propagation of optical wave either in the free space or in the optical system. This course is based on the result from the scalar diffraction theory to handle the interference and diffraction problems occured with the optical wave. In order to study more advanced courses, such as optical information processing or holographic optics, this course is the prerequisite course.“"}, "outline": {"ch": "1. Fourier Transforming and convolution.\n2. Linear and Space-invariant System.\n3. Scalar Diffraction Theory.\n4. Fresnel and Fraunhofer Diffraction.\n5. Fourier Transforming and Imaging Properies of Lenses.\n6. Frequency Analysis of Optical Imaging Systems.\n7. Spatial Filtering and Optical Information Processing.\n8. Holography.", "en": "1. Fourier Transforming and convolution.\n2. Linear and Space-invariant System.\n3. Scalar Diffraction Theory.\n4. Fresnel and Fraunhofer Diffraction.\n5. Fourier Transforming and Imaging Properies of Lenses.\n6. Frequency Analysis of Optical Imaging Systems.\n7. Spatial Filtering and Optical Information Processing.\n8. Holography."}, "textbook": {"ch": "Introduction to Fourier Optics by Goodman", "en": "Introduction to Fourie